ROUND 5 FEATURE MATCH: PIERRE DAGEN VS. VJERAN HORVAT
=====================================================



 Posted in [GRAND PRIX MILAN 2015](/en/events/coverage/gpmil15)
 on December 13, 2014 






![](https://media.magic.wizards.com/styles/auth_small/public/images/person/henke_author.jpg)
By Tobi Henke











These two—Frenchman Pierre Dagen and Croatia's Vjeran Horvat—had made it this far without a loss, but one of them would surely lose now. Dagen could boast three previous Grand Prix Top 8s, including a finals appearance just two weeks ago, whereas Horvat's major accomplishment so far was winning a Modern Grand Prix in Prague earlier this year.



Back then, Horvat had been playing a blue-white-red aggro-control deck featuring [Geist of Saint Traft](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Geist+of+Saint+Traft) and [Restoration Angel](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Restoration+Angel) for beatdown. Since then, most players have switched to [Delver of Secrets](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delver+of+Secrets) and [Young Pyromancer](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Young+Pyromancer) but Horvat stayed true to his cards. Dagen was playing a version of [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy) similar to the one popularized by deck designer Josh Utter-Leyton and his teammates at the World Championship. So, while both players were running Jeskai builds, the decks couldn't have been more different from each other.



**Game 1**



The match began with Dagen cycling through some cards via [Peek](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Peek), [Thought Scour](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thought+Scour), and [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm) discarding [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher). When Horvat made his first move and cast [Snapcaster Mage](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Snapcaster+Mage) at the end of Dagen's third turn, Dagen even increased his card selecting and resolved [Dig Through Time](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dig+Through+Time).


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Unsatisfied with the development of the game so far, Horvat finally decided to get something done on his turn four: he played [Celestial Colonnade](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Celestial+Colonnade) and tapped out for [Geist of Saint Traft](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Geist+of+Saint+Traft). Now it was all in Dagen's hand. If Dagen had the combo, all would be lost for Horvat, but if Horvat would be able to untap with 8 power worth of attackers, things would quickly go downhill for Dagen.



Dagen did have the combo. He unearthed [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher), cast [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy), and basically just won. The messy reality of it involved a [Gitaxian Probe](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gitaxian+Probe), an [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm), a [Treasure Cruise](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Treasure+Cruise), and another [Gitaxian Probe](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gitaxian+Probe), all interspersed with various [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy) triggers and the ability of [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher) untapping lands in between. [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy) allowed Dagen to dump a second [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher) and a third, which were both unearthed, and when it was obvious Dagen would neither run out of cards nor mana before growing his blue army to lethal proportions, Horvat conceded.



Pierre Dagen 1-0 Vjeran Horvat



**Game 2**



This time neither player had much action, no cantrips or otherwise, until Horvat summoned [Vendilion Clique](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vendilion+Clique) at the end of Dagen's turn three. Dagen stopped it with [Remand](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand), or rather delayed it until Horvat's main phase when he re-cast it and took a look at Dagen's hand: two lands, two copies of [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy), two lands, and three [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm)s …



Horvat swallowed, Dagen chuckled: "A very good hand against [Vendilion Clique](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vendilion+Clique), isn't it?"



Horvat took one Ascendancy anyway, then took the other with Wear & Tear after Dagen had cast it. [Vendilion Clique](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vendilion+Clique) died to [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm), but Horvat was able to establish a clock anyway in the form of [Restoration Angel](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Restoration+Angel).



Dagen tried to get his hand back into shape via [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm)s and [Serum Visions](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serum+Visions), but before he found a solution or another threat of his own second [Restoration Angel](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Restoration+Angel) sealed the deal.



Pierre Dagen 1-1 Vjeran Horvat



**Game 3**



Horvat opened on Relic of [Progenitus](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progenitus), a card Dagen hadn't seen before in the match and one that would make all of his [Dig Through Time](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dig+Through+Time) and [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher) along with the [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm) that much worse, especially when Horvat added a second Relic and was able to keep Dagen reliably at zero graveyard cards without ever having to crack one of the artifacts.


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Horvat even had a threat to go along with the disruption, if only a lowly [Snapcaster Mage](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Snapcaster+Mage). 2 points of damage did add up though. Meanwhile, Dagen scrambled to get back into the game. Through a couple of [Remand](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Remand)s, he managed to get a [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher) onto the battlefield the old-fashioned way by casting it from his hand. But the Stitcher died to [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt) before it was even used once and its brother met the same fate. It was even hit by the very same [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt) as a second [Snapcaster Mage](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Snapcaster+Mage) increased the pressure on Dagen.



Dagen might still have been able to get somewhere with his pair of [Faerie Conclave](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Faerie+Conclave)s, but before long he was forced to trade both away, blocking [Snapcaster Mage](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Snapcaster+Mage)s. Stuck with uncastable [Dig Through Time](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dig+Through+Time) in hand, Dagen lost soon after to [Restoration Angel](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Restoration+Angel).



Pierre Dagen 1-2 Vjeran Horvat



"This is a terrible matchup for me," said Dagen. "Especially after sideboarding." Horvat had just won his day's second match against [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy) and couldn't agree more.
